==English==
===Etymology===
From Italian ''[[diva#Italian|diva]]'' (goddess),  from Latin ''[[diva#Latin|diva]]'' (goddess), female of ''[[divus]]'' (divine, divine one).
===Noun===
[[Category:English irregular plurals]]
{{en-noun2|'''diva'''|'''[[dive]] '''or''' [[divas]]'''}}

#The principal female singer of an opera company, or opera star. 
#A principal female in some other field, a [[prima ballerina]]. 
#Any female celebrity, usually a well known pop singer. 
#A person who considers himself or herself much more important than others, has high expectations of others and becomes angry when their standards or demands are not met.

